# Keep the build context small and the image clean.
#
# data/ (raw listings.csv + the 1.4 GB calendar.csv + data/processed/) and logs/
# are large and/or runtime artifacts — they are NOT baked into the image; mount
# them at run time (-v "$PWD/data:/app/data"). app.py reads data/listings.csv at
# startup, so a data volume is required for `serve`/`ab`/`test`.
#
# models/ (small, ~1.5 MB) IS baked in so `serve` works out of the box; mount a
# models volume only when you want `pipeline` to persist freshly trained models.
data/
logs/

.venv/
venv/
.git/
.gitignore
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
*.egg-info/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
